value.def: Someone or something that is tender expresses gentle and caring feelings.

example.ex: Her voice was tender, full of pity...
example.tran: 她的声音很温柔，充满了怜爱。

example.ex: Patients may not receive the tender, loving care once associated with a hospital stay.
example.tran: 病人们可能享受不到以前住院时那种悉心体贴的照顾。

value.tran: 温柔的;慈爱的;体贴的;柔软的

example.ex: Mr. White tenderly embraced his wife.
example.tran: 怀特先生温柔地拥抱了妻子。

example.ex: She smiled, politely rather than with tenderness or gratitude.
example.tran: 她只是出于礼貌地笑了笑，而非出于关心或感激。

value.def: If you say that someone does something at a tender age, you mean that they do it when they are still young and have not had much experience.

example.ex: He had become attracted to the game at the tender age of seven.
example.tran: 他在7岁的小小年纪就喜欢上了这项运动。

example.ex: ...the loss of her father at such a tender age.
example.tran: 如此幼小的年纪就失去了父亲

value.def: Meat or other food that is tender is easy to cut or chew.

example.ex: Cook for a minimum of 2 hours, or until the meat is tender.
example.tran: 至少煮两个小时，或一直煮到肉变烂为止。

value.tran: (肉等食品)软的，嫩的，易咀嚼的

value.def: If part of your body is tender, it is sensitive and painful when it is touched.

example.ex: Treat any tender points by massaging.
example.tran: 用按摩法治疗疼痛部位。

value.tran: （身体部位）敏感的，疼痛的，一碰就疼的

example.ex: There is still some tenderness in her tummy.

value.def: A tender is a formal offer to supply goods or to do a particular job, and a statement of the price that you or your company will charge. If a contract is put out to tender, formal offers are invited. If a company wins a tender, their offer is accepted.

example.ex: Builders will then be sent the specifications and asked to submit a tender for the work...
example.tran: 建筑商们将会收到说明书，并被邀请参与该项目投标。

example.ex: Some services are now compulsorily put out to tender.
example.tran: 现在，有些服务项目必须进行招标。

example.ex: ...the consortium that has won the tender to build the second Severn Bridge.
example.tran: 中标得以建造第二座塞文桥的财团

value.def: If a company tenders for something, it makes a formal offer to supply goods or do a job for a particular price.

example.ex: The staff are forbidden to tender for private-sector work...
example.tran: 工作人员不得投标承接私营部门的工作。

example.ex: He tendered for and was awarded the contract.
example.tran: 他参与竞标，并赢得了合同。

example.ex: ...compulsory competitive tendering for council leisure and recreation services.
example.tran: 对市政会休闲娱乐服务项目的强制性竞标

value.def: If you tender something such as a suggestion, your resignation, or money, you formally offer or present it.

example.ex: He took his wallet from his inside coat pocket and tendered the permit.
example.tran: 他从外套内兜里掏出钱包，出示了许可证。
